Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: https://medium.com/@LuxorTechTeam/unlock-your-asic-potential-with-efudd-x-luxor-672e73a1d185

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: pretty interesting to see pools working with Efudd firmware

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: article also mentions Pirate and KMD by name

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: 20% more hashrate from same hardware!?

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: Efudd firmware usually takes a % dev fee but evidently they have something worked out with Luxor, I think the default is 4%

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: so on Luxor people will only pay 1% dev fee, and 0.5% to start. It's an interesting way to attract miners to your pool and your hashrate-boosting firmware

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: I think because they let you adjust hashrate + voltage on each board, that let's it squeeze more hash out. Default UI must run all boards at the same speed/voltage

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: it's especially good for later batches, which often just have 1 "bad" board that makes the entire rig run slower

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: I am not sure it's worth it to run efudd firmware on batch 1's, they can run at max speed already
